The George Brown College Safe Walk team is a service offered by the Student Association and the college to help students, staff, and guests feel safer on campus, especially during evenings. This service can be contacted at SafeWalkCoord@Sagbc.ca or 1-888-210-7233 (call, text, or WhatsApp). The team operates at several locations: St. James at 300 Adelaide Street E., Casa Loma at 160 Kendal Ave., Waterfront at 51 Dockside Dr., and Daniels Waterfront at 3 Lower Jarvis St. The service does not operate during winter and spring breaks, as well as days the college is closed.
